&lt;/div>&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/33299302/composer-update-failed-out-of-memory">https://stackoverflow.com/questions/33299302/composer-update-failed-out-of-memory&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Katiak&amp;rsquo;s answer worked but I had to modify it. You will need 4 GB of free space for this to work on a Linux machine. Make sure you sudo the commands if you&amp;rsquo;re not root:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">2
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">3
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback">/bin/dd if=/dev/zero of=/var/swap.1 bs=1M count=4096
/sbin/mkswap /var/swap.1
/sbin/swapon /var/swap.1
&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
